      "P.C. Richard & Son began as a small hardware store in Bensonhurst, Brooklyn in 1909, founded by Dutch immigrant, Peter Christian Richard. It was transformed by his son, A.J., into what is now America's #1 family owned appliance, electronics and mattress, retailer with 66 showrooms serving New York, New Jersey, Connecticut and Pennsylvania.\r\n\r\nHeadquartered in Farmingdale, LI, NY, where P.C. Richard & Son has its main distribution center, the company has over 1 million square feet of warehousing in NY, NJ & CT, plus 3 owned and operated state-of-the-art service facilities for repairs on appliances and electronics. In Bridgeport, CT, P.C. Richard & Son operates a 70,000 sq. foot distribution/training/service center that services the Connecticut market.\r\n\r\nCustomers can find  the largest selection and the guaranteed lowest prices on a wide variety of exciting products at P.C. Richard & Son, from major appliances and consumer electronics, including Refrigerators, Washers & Dryers, 4K UHD TV's, HDTV’s, Digital Cameras, Computers, iPads, tablets, Video Games…and now mattresses!\r\n\r\nAll of P.C. Richard & Son's nearly 2,827 employees are dedicated to providing Superior Service Before, During and After the Sale, and giving our customers a wonderful and rewarding shopping experience. It starts with friendly and knowledgeable salespeople, who explain on all the features of today's high-tech products, next day delivery, as well as professional installation and repair service by our very own crews.\r\n\r\nThe company is currently run by the 5th generation of the Richard family. P.C. Richard & Son is built on a 105-year tradition...Richard IS Reliable. Visit us on the web at www.pcrichard.com.",
